this is how we use it in pldm, I dont have this change in gerrit yet-

we call the below API to find a FRU/PDR from a given RSI and gave the entity structure fields. We know that is the entity which needs to be removed so we save it as removeEntity.

pldm_pdr_fru_record_set_find_by_rsi(pdrRepo, rsi, &terminusHdl, &entityType,
                                    &entityInsNum, &containerId, false);
    removeEntity.entity_type = entityType;
    removeEntity.entity_instance_num = entityInsNum;
    removeEntity.entity_container_id = containerId;

we then pass removeEntity into our API so that it can be removed from the entity association tree.

auto removeBmcEntityRc = pldm_entity_association_pdr_remove_contained_entity(pdrRepo, &removeEntity, false, &updateRecordHdlBmc);

This is the only place we use this API for now.

I dont think we need to take care of endian conversion here when comparing entity fields because when we extract it in pldm_pdr_fru_record_set_find_by_rsi API we are doing the endian conversion. Please correct me if I am wrong

